  "statement": "Let n\\ge 2 and let C = I_n - \\tfrac{1}{n}J_n, where J_n is the all-ones matrix (so C subtracts the coordinate average from each entry of a vector). \n(a) Find \\operatorname{rank} C and the dimension of the solution space of C\\mathbf x = \\mathbf 0.\n(b) For a given \\mathbf b\\in\\mathbb R^n, give a necessary and sufficient condition for C\\mathbf x = \\mathbf b to be consistent, and describe the full solution set when it is.",
