  "trap": "Seeing $C=I-\\frac1nJ$ with its $n$ visibly nonzero rows tempts the conclusion \"rank $n$\" (it *looks* like a perturbed identity). The reality is that $C$ is a **projection**, idempotent with a one-dimensional kernel spanned by $\\mathbf 1$, so its rank is $n-1$. A second trap in part (b) is to test consistency by checking $\\det C\\neq0$ — it is $0$, so Cramer is useless — and then to forget that for a *singular* system one must verify $\\mathbf b\\in\\operatorname{Col}(C)$, here the hyperplane $\\sum b_i=0$.",
