     "**Attainability.** Take $A=\\operatorname{diag}(I_r,0)$ (so $\\operatorname{Col}A=\\operatorname{span}(e_1,\\dots,e_r)$). Build $B$ of rank $s$ by placing $k$ of its pivot rows among the first $r$ rows and the remaining $s-k$ pivot rows among rows $r+1,\\dots,n$ (possible precisely when $s-k\\le n-r$ and $k\\le r$, i.e. $\\max(0,r+s-n)\\le k\\le\\min(r,s)$).",
