     "Here $x_i=i,\\ y_j=j$, so $\\prod_{i<j}(x_j-x_i)=\\prod_{i<j}(j-i)=\\prod_{k=1}^{n-1}k!$ (the superfactorial), and likewise for the $y$'s — the numerator is its square.",
