     "For $n=3$: numerator $=(1!\\,2!)^2=4$; denominator $=\\prod_{i,j=1}^{3}(i+j)=(2\\cdot3\\cdot4)(3\\cdot4\\cdot5)(4\\cdot5\\cdot6)=24\\cdot60\\cdot120=172800.$",
