     "Taking determinants gives $\\det M=\\det A\\,\\det S$. Since $M$ and $A$ are invertible, $\\det S=\\det M/\\det A\\ne0$, so $S$ is invertible.",
     "Invert each factor (the unitriangular ones invert by negating their off-diagonal block) and multiply in reverse order: $M^{-1}=\\begin{pmatrix} I & -A^{-1}B \\\\ 0 & I\\end{pmatrix}\\begin{pmatrix} A^{-1} & 0 \\\\ 0 & S^{-1}\\end{pmatrix}\\begin{pmatrix} I & 0 \\\\ -CA^{-1} & I\\end{pmatrix}$.",
