     "Since $(I_n+J_n)^{-1}=I_n-\\tfrac{1}{1+n}J_n$ (Sherman–Morrison on $I+\\mathbf 1\\mathbf 1^{\\mathsf T}$), and $J_n\\mathbf 1=n\\mathbf 1$, we get $(I_n+J_n)^{-1}\\mathbf 1=\\mathbf 1-\\tfrac{n}{1+n}\\mathbf 1=\\tfrac{1}{1+n}\\mathbf 1$.",
     "So $\\mathbf 1^{\\mathsf T}(I_n+J_n)^{-1}\\mathbf 1=\\tfrac{1}{1+n}\\,\\mathbf 1^{\\mathsf T}\\mathbf 1=\\tfrac{n}{1+n}$, hence $S=2-\\tfrac{n}{1+n}=\\tfrac{n+2}{n+1}$.",
