     "$\\det A=\\det(I_n+J_n)=1+n$ (eigenvalue $1+n$ once on $\\mathbf 1$, eigenvalue $1$ with multiplicity $n-1$), and by the Schur formula $\\det M=\\det(A)\\,S$ with $S$ the scalar Schur complement.",
     "From part (b)'s computation, $\\det M=(1+n)\\cdot\\tfrac{n+2}{n+1}=n+2$.",
