     "Taking traces and using $\\operatorname{tr}(A)=\\operatorname{tr}(uv^{\\top})=v^{\\top}u=t$, we get $\\operatorname{tr}(A^k)=t^{k-1}\\operatorname{tr}(A)=t^{k-1}\\cdot t=t^k$.",
     "The characteristic polynomial of $A$ is $\\chi_A(x)=x^{n-1}(x-t)$ (rank $1$ kills $n-1$ eigenvalues; the trace pins the last at $t$), so $\\det(I_n+A)=(-1)^n\\chi_A(-1)=(-1)^n(-1)^{n-1}(-1-t)=1+t$. This holds for every $A$, diagonalisable or not.",
