  "remark": "**Insight.** Rank-one matrices linearise: $A^2=(\\operatorname{tr}A)A$ turns matrix powers into scalar powers, so the whole power-sum sequence $\\operatorname{tr}(A^k)=t^k$ is read off a single scalar. The case $t=0$ is the instructive edge — $A$ is then a nonzero *nilpotent* (a single $2\\times2$ Jordan block padded with zeros), so spectral arguments that quietly assume diagonalisability break, yet the characteristic-polynomial route survives untouched. This 'trace geyser' underlies the Sherman–Morrison formula and the matrix-determinant lemma $\\det(I+uv^{\\top})=1+v^{\\top}u$."
