    "name": "Gram determinant / Cauchy-Schwarz",
    "steps": [
     "Form the Gram matrix $G=A^{\\mathsf T}A=\\begin{pmatrix} c_1\\cdot c_1 & c_1\\cdot c_2 \\\\ c_2\\cdot c_1 & c_2\\cdot c_2 \\end{pmatrix}$. Then $\\det G=(\\det A)^2$ since $\\det(A^{\\mathsf T}A)=(\\det A)^2.$",
     "Compute $\\det G=\\|c_1\\|^2\\|c_2\\|^2-(c_1\\cdot c_2)^2$. Hence the exact identity $(\\det A)^2=\\|c_1\\|^2\\|c_2\\|^2-(c_1\\cdot c_2)^2\\le\\|c_1\\|^2\\|c_2\\|^2.$",
     "This is precisely the **Cauchy-Schwarz** slack written as an equality. Taking roots gives $|\\det A|\\le\\|c_1\\|\\|c_2\\|$, with equality $\\iff c_1\\cdot c_2=0$, i.e. $c_1\\perp c_2$. $\\blacksquare$"
    ]
