  "statement": "Let $A,B$ be real symmetric **positive-definite** $n\\times n$ matrices. Prove the superadditivity of the $n$-th root of the determinant:\n$$\\bigl(\\det(A+B)\\bigr)^{1/n}\\;\\ge\\;(\\det A)^{1/n}+(\\det B)^{1/n},$$\nand determine when equality holds.",
  "answer": "The inequality holds for all positive-definite $A,B$; equality $\\iff B=cA$ for some scalar $c>0$ (the matrices are proportional).",
