  "statement": "Let $A$ be a real $n\\times n$ matrix all of whose entries satisfy $|a_{ij}|\\le 1$. Prove the Hadamard determinant bound\n$$\\bigl|\\det A\\bigr|\\;\\le\\;n^{n/2},$$\nand show that equality is attainable $\\iff$ a **Hadamard matrix** of order $n$ exists, i.e. a $\\pm1$ matrix with mutually orthogonal rows. (In particular equality holds for $n=2$ and $n=4$, but not for $n=3$.)",
