     "The subtracted matrix $B^\\top A^{-1}B$ is PSD (as $A^{-1}\\succ0$), and $C=S+B^\\top A^{-1}B$ with both summands $\\succeq0$. **Determinant monotonicity** on PD matrices: if $C\\succeq S\\succ0$ then $\\det C\\ge\\det S$ (eigenvalues of $S^{-1/2}CS^{-1/2}=I+S^{-1/2}B^\\top A^{-1}BS^{-1/2}$ are all $\\ge1$, so its determinant is $\\ge1$).",
     "Therefore $\\det(C-B^\\top A^{-1}B)=\\det S\\le\\det C$, giving $\\det M=\\det A\\,\\det S\\le\\det A\\,\\det C.$",
     "Equality forces $\\det S=\\det C$, hence $\\det(I+S^{-1/2}B^\\top A^{-1}BS^{-1/2})=1$; since every eigenvalue is $\\ge1$ they must all equal $1$, so $B^\\top A^{-1}B=0$, and as $A^{-1}\\succ0$ this gives $B=0$. $\\boxed{\\det M\\le\\det A\\det C,\\ \\text{equality}\\iff B=0}$"
