     "Write $\\widetilde L=nI_{n-1}-\\mathbf 1\\mathbf 1^{\\top}$, a rank-one update of the invertible scalar matrix $nI_{n-1}$.",
     "The matrix-determinant lemma gives $\\det(nI-\\mathbf 1\\mathbf 1^\\top)=\\det(nI)\\,\\big(1-\\mathbf 1^\\top (nI)^{-1}\\mathbf 1\\big)=n^{\\,n-1}\\big(1-\\tfrac{n-1}{n}\\big)$, using $\\mathbf 1^\\top(nI)^{-1}\\mathbf 1=\\tfrac{n-1}{n}$ since $\\mathbf 1$ has $n-1$ entries.",
     "This equals $n^{\\,n-1}\\cdot \\tfrac1n=n^{\\,n-2}$, recovering Cayley's formula. $\\boxed{n^{\\,n-2}}$"
