  "answer": "$$\\big(A^k\\big)_{uu}=\\frac{1}{2^{d}}\\sum_{j=0}^{d}\\binom{d}{j}(d-2j)^{k},\\qquad \\operatorname{tr}(A^k)=\\sum_{j=0}^{d}\\binom{d}{j}(d-2j)^{k}.$$",
  "trap": "Multiplying out $A^k$ directly for a $2^d\\times 2^d$ matrix, or trying to enumerate walks coordinate-by-coordinate without symmetry. The key insight is that $A=\\sum_{b=1}^d I\\otimes\\cdots\\otimes X\\otimes\\cdots\\otimes I$ (a sum of single-bit flips), so $A$ is a tensor sum whose spectrum is $\\{d-2j\\}$ with binomial multiplicities; ignoring the tensor structure and brute-forcing dooms you.",
