     "Each $X$ has eigenvalues $\\pm1$; the eigenvalues of $A$ are sums $\\sum_b \\epsilon_b$ with $\\epsilon_b\\in\\{+1,-1\\}$, i.e. $d-2j$ where $j$ = number of $-1$s, with multiplicity $\\binom dj$.",
     "Closed walks from a single vertex: by vertex-transitivity all diagonal entries are equal, so $(A^k)_{uu}=\\tfrac{1}{2^d}\\operatorname{tr}(A^k)=\\tfrac1{2^d}\\sum_{j=0}^d\\binom dj (d-2j)^k$, and $\\operatorname{tr}(A^k)=\\sum_{j=0}^d\\binom dj(d-2j)^k$. $\\boxed{\\tfrac1{2^d}\\sum_j\\binom dj(d-2j)^k}$"
