  "statement": "Let $a_1,\\dots,a_n$ be any $n$ integers and let $V$ be the integer Vandermonde matrix $V_{ij}=a_i^{\\,j-1}$ ($1\\le i,j\\le n$), so $\\det V=\\prod_{1\\le i<j\\le n}(a_j-a_i)$. Prove that the superfactorial $$\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}k!\\;=\\;0!\\,1!\\,2!\\cdots(n-1)!$$ divides $\\det V$, for every choice of integers $a_i$.",
  "answer": "For all integers $a_1,\\dots,a_n$, $$\\Big(\\textstyle\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}k!\\Big)\\ \\Big|\\ \\det V=\\prod_{1\\le i<j\\le n}(a_j-a_i),$$ and the bound is sharp (equality up to sign when $a_i=i$). $\\textbf{proved}$",
