  "remark": "**Insight.** Cayley-Hamilton turns a *matrix* equation into two *scalar* equations on trace and determinant — the cleanest tool for $2\\times2$ classification. The polynomial $x^2-x-1$ is the golden recurrence; its companion matrix $\\begin{pmatrix}1&1\\\\1&0\\end{pmatrix}$ generates Fibonacci numbers via $F^n=\\begin{pmatrix}F_{n+1}&F_n\\\\F_n&F_{n-1}\\end{pmatrix}$, and indeed $A^2=A+I$ mirrors $F_{n+1}=F_n+F_{n-1}$."
