     "\\textbf{Scalar idempotents:} $A=cI$ with $c^2=c\\Rightarrow c\\in\\{0,1\\}$ — exactly $2$ matrices, namely $0$ and $I$ (with traces $0$ and $2$).",
     "\\textbf{Non-scalar:} write $A=\\begin{pmatrix}a&b\\\\ c&1-a\\end{pmatrix}$ (trace $1$) with $\\det A=a(1-a)-bc=0$, i.e. $bc=a(1-a)$. No scalar matrix has trace $1$, so this whole family is automatically non-scalar; we just count its size.",
