     "Each of $A,B,C$ is traceless (shown above), so all three lie in the $3$-dimensional space $\\mathfrak{sl}_2(\\mathbb{R})$. Together with $I$ they would form a basis $\\{I,A,B,C\\}$ of $M_2(\\mathbb{R})$ obeying the quaternion multiplication table — i.e. realise $\\mathbb{H}$ as $2\\times2$ real matrices.",
