     "Now commute $X$ with $S=E_{ij}+E_{ji}$ ($i\\neq j$): $XS$ has $(i,j)$-entry $x_i$, while $SX$ has $(i,j)$-entry $x_j$. Equality forces $x_i=x_j$.",
