     "A matrix for which every nonzero vector is an eigenvector must be scalar: write $Xv=\\lambda(v)\\,v$. For independent $u,w$ we have $X(u+w)=\\lambda(u+w)(u+w)$, and also $=\\lambda(u)u+\\lambda(w)w$; comparing coefficients on the basis $u,w$ forces $\\lambda(u)=\\lambda(u+w)=\\lambda(w)$.",
