     "**If $p+s=2$:** put $s=2-p$, let $a=p-1$ so $s=1-a$; then $p^2+qr=2p-1$ becomes $a^2+qr=0$. With $b=q,\\,c=r$ this is the cone $a^2+bc=0$ — the full Jordan family. $\\blacksquare$"
