     "Therefore $\\tau(W_n)=\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}\\big(3-2\\cos\\tfrac{2\\pi k}{n}\\big)$. Factor $3-2\\cos\\theta=\\alpha^{-1}|\\,\\alpha-e^{i\\theta}|^2$ with $\\alpha=\\tfrac{3+\\sqrt5}2$ the root of $\\alpha+\\alpha^{-1}=3$.",
     "Using $\\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}(\\alpha-\\omega^k)=\\alpha^n-1$ for the $n$-th roots of unity $\\omega^k$, and the same identity for the conjugates, the product telescopes to $\\prod_k(3-2\\cos\\theta_k)=\\alpha^{-n}(\\alpha^n-1)^2$, which simplifies to $\\alpha^n+\\alpha^{-n}-2$.",
     "Since $\\alpha=\\tfrac{3+\\sqrt5}2$, $\\alpha^{-1}=\\tfrac{3-\\sqrt5}2$, we get $\\boxed{\\tau(W_n)=\\big(\\tfrac{3+\\sqrt5}2\\big)^n+\\big(\\tfrac{3-\\sqrt5}2\\big)^n-2}$, an integer $L_{2n}-2$."
